{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T09:13:17.617Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "CUDA Basics — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What CUDA Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CUDA (Compute Unified Device Architecture)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a parallel computing platform and programming model developed by NVIDIA that enables dramatic increases in computing performance by harnessing the power of the GPU."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA allows developers to use CUDA-enabled GPUs for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "general-purpose computing"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (GPGPU), not just graphics, unlocking the true potential of deep neural networks behind artificial intelligence."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why CUDA Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA has "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "revolutionized the world"}, {"type": "text", "text": " by allowing humans to compute large blocks of data in parallel, which unlocked the true potential of deep neural networks:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA Impact"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Deep Learning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Enables training of massive models (transformers, LLMs)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AI Models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Processes billions of operations in parallel"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scientific Computing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High-performance computing for simulations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Image Generation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast inference for diffusion models, GANs"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Modern GPUs are measured in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "teraflops"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (trillions of floating-point operations per second) — unlike CPUs with 24 cores, a modern GPU like the RTX 4090 has "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "over 16,000 cores"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CPU vs GPU in CUDA"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CPU (Host)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU (Device)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Name in CUDA"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Host"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Device"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Design"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Versatile, general computing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast parallel computation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cores"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "24 cores (e.g., Intel i9)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "16,000+ cores (e.g., RTX 4090)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Task Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Serial tasks, OS, I/O"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Parallel workloads, matrix math"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Memory"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Separate RAM"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Separate GPU memory"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA Memory Model"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CPU (Host)              GPU (Device)\n    |                      |\n    RAM (Main Memory)     GPU Memory\n    |                      |\n    ←── Copy Data ──→     ←── Process ──→"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Both host and device have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "separate memory spaces"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Host memory"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Main RAM\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Device memory"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": GPU memory\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data transfer"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Must copy data between host and device"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How CUDA Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Workflow"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Write a kernel"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": C function that runs on all GPU threads"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Copy data to GPU"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Transfer from host memory to device memory"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Execute kernel"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Run on device with specified blocks and threads"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Copy results back"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Transfer from device to host"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Repeat or finish"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Continue training or complete"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA Execution Model"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU\n├── Streaming Multiprocessors (SMs)\n    ├── Each SM has 8-64 CUDA cores [web:213]\n    ├── Hundreds of threads per SM [web:213]\n    └── Threads take turns if more than capacity [web:213]\n\nThread\n├── Runs single computation [web:213]\n├── Shares memory/code with other threads [web:213]\n├── Limited thread-local memory (registers) [web:213]\n└── Much simpler/slower than CPU cores [web:213]\n\nBlock\n├── Collection of up to 1024 threads [web:213]\n├── All threads run same code [web:213]\n├── Has shared fast memory (48KB) [web:213]\n└── Organized in 1-D, 2-D, or 3-D grid [web:213]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA Kernels"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What is a Kernel?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CUDA kernel"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a function that runs on the GPU, defined with the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__global__"}, {"type": "text", "text": " specifier."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "cpp"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "// CUDA kernel (runs on GPU)\n__global__ void addVectors(float* a, float* b, float* c, int n) {\n    // Calculate global thread index\n    int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;\n    \n    if (i < n) {\n        c[i] = a[i] + b[i];  // Parallel computation [web:215]\n    }\n}"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Kernel Launch Syntax"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "cpp"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "// Launch kernel on GPU\n// <<< blocks, threads_per_block >>> is CUDA extension\naddVectors<<< num_blocks, threads_per_block >>>(a, b, c, n);"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The triple brackets:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Allocate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " blocks and threads per block\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Copy code"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to GPU card\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Set"}, {"type": "text", "text": " "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "blockDim"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "blockIdx"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "threadIdx"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for kernel"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA in PyTorch (Deep Learning Frameworks)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In PyTorch, CUDA is used "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "automatically"}, {"type": "text", "text": " when you place tensors on GPU:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\n# Create tensor on CPU (default)\ntensor_cpu = torch.randn(1000, 1000)\n\n# Move tensor to GPU (device placement)\ntensor_gpu = tensor_cpu.to('cuda')  # or tensor_cpu.cuda()\n\n# All operations automatically run on GPU\nresult = tensor_gpu @ tensor_gpu.T  # Matrix multiplication on GPU"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Device Placement"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Check CUDA availability\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\n    device = torch.device('cuda')\n    print(f\"Using GPU: {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)}\")\nelse:\n    device = torch.device('cpu')\n\n# Place model on GPU\nmodel = torch.nn.Linear(100, 10).to(device)\n\n# Place input on GPU\ninput = torch.randn(64, 100).to(device)\n\n# Forward pass runs on GPU\noutput = model(input)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batched Computation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Batch size: process 64 samples at once\nbatch_size = 64\ninput_batch = torch.randn(batch_size, 100).to(device)\n\n# GPU processes all 64 samples in parallel\noutput_batch = model(input_batch)  # Batched computation on GPU"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU is ideal for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "batched computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " because it processes entire batches simultaneously rather than sequentially."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA Programming in C++"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complete Example"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "cpp"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "#include <cuda_runtime.h>\n#include <stdio.h>\n\n// CUDA kernel (runs on GPU)\n__global__ void addVectors(float* a, float* b, float* c, int n) {\n    int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;\n    if (i < n) {\n        c[i] = a[i] + b[i];\n    }\n}\n\nint main() {\n    int n = 1000000;\n    float* a, *b, *c;\n    \n    // Allocate host memory\n    a = new float[n];\n    b = new float[n];\n    c = new float[n];\n    \n    // Initialize data\n    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n        a[i] = i;\n        b[i] = i * 2;\n    }\n    \n    // Allocate device memory\n    float* d_a, *d_b, *d_c;\n    cudaMalloc(&d_a, n * sizeof(float));\n    cudaMalloc(&d_b, n * sizeof(float));\n    cudaMalloc(&d_c, n * sizeof(float));\n    \n    // Copy data to GPU\n    cudaMemcpy(d_a, a, n * sizeof(float), cudaMemcpyHostToDevice);\n    cudaMemcpy(d_b, b, n * sizeof(float), cudaMemcpyHostToDevice);\n    \n    // Launch kernel (blocks, threads_per_block)\n    int threads_per_block = 256;\n    int num_blocks = (n + threads_per_block - 1) / threads_per_block;\n    addVectors<<< num_blocks, threads_per_block >>> (d_a, d_b, d_c, n);\n    \n    // Wait for GPU to finish\n    cudaDeviceSynchronize();  // Required for GPU code [web:214]\n    \n    // Copy results back to host\n    cudaMemcpy(c, d_c, n * sizeof(float), cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost);\n    \n    // Free memory\n    cudaFree(d_a);\n    cudaFree(d_b);\n    cudaFree(d_c);\n    \n    delete[] a;\n    delete[] b;\n    delete[] c;\n    \n    return 0;\n}"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compilation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Compile CUDA code with nvcc (CUDA compiler)\nnvcc -o add_vectors add_vectors.cu\n\n# Run\n./add_vectors"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key CUDA Concepts"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Concept"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Host"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CPU that launches CUDA kernels"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Device"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU that executes CUDA kernels"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Kernel"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Function that runs on GPU ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__global__"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Thread"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single execution unit on GPU"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Block"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Group of threads (up to 1024)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Grid"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Collection of blocks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Shared Memory"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast memory per block (48KB)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Global Memory"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Main GPU memory (slower)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Registers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Thread-local memory"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA Best Practices"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. GPU Jobs Should Be Compute-Bound"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU jobs should be compute-bound:\n- Lots of math, few memory transfers [web:213]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Memory transfers are expensive"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Do as much as possible on GPU without transferring data\n- Run multiple kernels after one another without moving data"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Large Fixed Transfer Cost"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA has large, fixed transfer cost:\n→ For small amounts of work, a single CPU core is faster [web:213]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Even for 8 dot products, time is dominated by data transfer."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Practical Speed Improvement"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practical GPU speed improvement is usually less than 3-4 times CPU [web:213]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Despite 16,000 cores vs 24 cores, real speedup is limited by memory transfer overhead."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA Synchronization"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "cpp"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "// GPU code is asynchronous — must synchronize\ncudaDeviceSynchronize();  // Pause and wait for GPU to complete [web:214]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why required"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": GPU execution is asynchronous — the CPU continues while GPU runs the kernel. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "cudaDeviceSynchronize()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " pauses execution and waits for GPU completion."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of CUDA as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "a factory with many workers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Host (CEO)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CPU that plans and assigns tasks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Device (Workshop)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": GPU with 16,000 workers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Kernel (Task)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Work instruction given to all workers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Threads (Workers)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Each performs one computation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Blocks (Teams)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Groups of workers (up to 1024)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Grid (Factory)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": All teams working together"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Memory Transfer (Shipping)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Moving materials between offices"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CUDA"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Parallel computing platform by NVIDIA for GPU computing"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Host"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CPU that launches CUDA kernels"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Device"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": GPU that executes CUDA kernels"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Kernel"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Function with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "__global__"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that runs on GPU"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Thread"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Single execution unit (simpler/slower than CPU cores)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Block"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Group of up to 1024 threads with shared memory (48KB)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Grid"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Collection of blocks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Separate memory"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Host RAM and GPU memory are separate"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data transfer"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Must copy data between host and device"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Thrust triple brackets"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<<< blocks, threads >>>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " launch kernel"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "nvcc"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CUDA compiler for.cu files"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Async execution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": GPU runs asynchronously, need "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "cudaDeviceSynchronize()"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PyTorch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".to('cuda')"}, {"type": "text", "text": " places tensor on GPU"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batched computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": GPU processes entire batches in parallel"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Compute-bound"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": GPU jobs need lots of math, few transfers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transfer cost"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Large fixed cost — small work better on CPU"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Speedup"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Usually <3-4x CPU despite 16,000 cores"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "16,000 cores"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": RTX 4090 has over 16,000 CUDA cores"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Teraflops"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": GPUs measure in trillions of FLOPs per second"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Deep learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CUDA unlocks true potential of neural networks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "foundation of modern AI"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — without it, training large models like transformers and LLMs would be impractical, as GPUs can process billions of operations in parallel while CPUs with 24 cores cannot match this throughput."}]}]}}